gobblin.cluster

Class GobblinClusterManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.cluster.GobblinClusterManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ApplicationLauncher, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    @Alpha
public class GobblinClusterManager
extends Object
implements ApplicationLauncher
    The central cluster manager for Gobblin Clusters.

    This class runs the GobblinHelixJobScheduler for scheduling and running Gobblin jobs. This class serves as the Helix controller and it uses a HelixManager to work with Helix.

    This class will initiates a graceful shutdown of the cluster in the following conditions:

    • A shutdown request is received via a Helix message of subtype HelixMessageSubTypes.APPLICATION_MASTER_SHUTDOWN. Upon receiving such a message, it will call stop() to initiate a graceful shutdown of the cluster
    • The shutdown hook gets called. The shutdown hook will call stop(), which will start a graceful shutdown of the cluster.
